    note right of maybeUnbound
        Socket may be unbound (DatagramSocketImpl constructor or null SocketAddress).
        bind() throws SocketException if already bound.
        connect() will auto-bind if socket is unbound.
    end note

    note right of BoundConnected
        Socket is bound and connected to a remote address.
        send/receive only exchange with connected remote address.
        disconnect() returns to BoundUnconnected state.
    end note

    note right of Closed
        Terminal state. setOption/getOption throw IOException if closed.
        isBound/isConnected/getInetAddress/getPort/getRemoteSocketAddress
        continue to return previous values after close.
    end note
